ACL Year-ROUND mentorship

Overview

We are a mentorship network that helps and supports junior researchers in natural language processing (NLP). Our aim is to promote equal access to advice on NLP career choices, initiating research in NLP, etc. People from all over the world can apply.


For more information, see our introduction, organizers, apply to join us, and a list of resources.

Introduction


What Is ACL Year-Round Mentorship?


This is an initiative undertaken under the auspices of the Association for Computational Linguistics, aimed to provide mentorship opportunities for students starting in the field. We are organizing virtual mentorship meetings throughout the year, with mentors from academia or industry with significant expertise and successful careers in Computational Linguistics. The topics discussed range from “how to choose research topic?” and “how to write a paper?” all the way to “should I do a PhD?” and “how do you keep a work-life balance?”


Who Can Apply?

Anyone who is currently an active student anywhere in the world can sign up to participate in mentorship sessions. We are currently unable to offer mentorship to people who are not currently enrolled as students.


When Are the Mentoring Events?

Mentorship sessions will be announced on this site. Registration is required and some sessions may be capped. Keep an eye out for future sessions of interest.

ACL mentoring session in July 2020.
